## Gotchas

- `codex exec` with inline prompt args can hang on stdin; pipe the prompt via echo instead
- Codex reviews read *every* file it can find — a thorough 200k-token review takes ~3 minutes

## Workflow

- Commit directly to main for framework iteration; use PRs for larger changes
- Run Codex review (`/ask-codex`) on non-trivial changes before committing
- When renaming across many files, do a final sweep with `rg` to catch stale references — they hide in README, hooks docs, and cross-skill references
- After updating skills/commands, run a Codex final-state review to catch inconsistencies between docs and actual files

## Things we've tried and rejected

- Cherry-pick by commit in sync-upstream — rejected because upstream commits can touch both framework and project files
- Blanket `docs/` in the sync allowlist — rejected because users put PRDs and ADRs there

